<script type="application/json" id="jsonMostPopular">{"objNews":{"aMDay":[{"issueDateStr":"Feb 11, 2026","publicationId":3,"dataId":313889,"subtitle":"Matt Kettmann","title":"Goleta Farming Visionaries Jay and Kristen Ruskey Both Die","summary":"Jay and Kristen Ruskey -- who pioneered California's coffee-growing movement from their farm in the hills of western Goleta -- both died suddenly on Sunday due to what's being described as a \"tragic accident.\" The co-founders of Frinj Coffee helped develop more than 70 coffee farms across Southern California based on what they learned at Good Land Organics, their farming operation atop Farren Road where the Ruskeys also tested now-popular exotic crops such as caviar limes and dragon fruit.","requestCount":4561},{"issueDateStr":"Feb 19, 2026","publicationId":3,"dataId":314206,"subtitle":"brewbound - paywall","title":"Breakthru Beverage Lays Off 500 Workers Amid Industry Shakeup","summary":"'Breakthru Beverage Group has undergone a \"strategic review\" of the company's \"overall business,\" according to a memo sent to employees by CEO Tom Bené on Tuesday, leading to layoffs of approximately 500 people, sources confirmed to Brewbound. Employees reported layoffs in several markets on the Reddit thread r/BreakthruBev. Sources confirmed the layoffs were closer to half of the rumored 1,000 employees cut.'","requestCount":2928},{"issueDateStr":"Jan 29, 2026","publicationId":3,"dataId":313339,"subtitle":"Esther Mobley, SF Chronicle, paywall","title":"After leaving California, one of the country's largest alcohol distributors is in shambles","summary":"'No winery, brewery or distillery wants to be caught on a sinking ship, it seems.'","requestCount":2866},{"issueDateStr":"Feb 19, 2026","publicationId":3,"dataId":314213,"subtitle":"Jess Lander, SF Chronicle paywall","title":"Gallo closing the Ranch Winery, laying off workers at four other locations","summary":"Gallo is closing a Napa Valley production facility and has planned layoffs at four other California wineries and tasting rooms, resulting in the loss of 93 jobs. Gallo will permanently close the Ranch Winery and cut staff at Louis M. Martini Winery and the Orin Swift tasting room, J Vineyards and Frei Ranch, another large production facility. Layoffs will impact a variety of departments, including winemaking, hospitality and culinary.","requestCount":2855},{"issueDateStr":"Feb 9, 2026","publicationId":3,"dataId":313736,"subtitle":"WineBusiness News","title":"Monarch Tractor Abandons Ship","summary":"The manufacturer of \"the world's first fully electric, driver-optional (autonomous), smart tractor\" is on the verge of going out of business. The Livermore, CA office phone still rings but nobody answers or returns voicemails. Most, if not all, of the employees are gone and the company is liquidating inventory via auction this week.","requestCount":2345},{"issueDateStr":"Jan 22, 2026","publicationId":3,"dataId":313038,"subtitle":"Esther Mobley, SF Chronicle, paywall","title":"An Acclaimed California Winery, Once a Darling of the Pinot Noir Movement, is Closing","summary":"Healdsburg's Arista Winery did not produce any wine during last year's harvest and will not produce any more in the future. Its final vintage will be 2024.","requestCount":2255}],"aYDay":[{"issueDateStr":"Feb 20, 2026","publicationId":3,"dataId":314320,"subtitle":"NBC News","title":"Supreme Court strikes down most of Trump's tariffs in a major blow to the president","summary":"The decision does not affect all of Trump's tariffs but invalidates those implemented using an emergency law.","requestCount":2032},{"issueDateStr":"Feb 19, 2026","publicationId":3,"dataId":314206,"subtitle":"brewbound - paywall","title":"Breakthru Beverage Lays Off 500 Workers Amid Industry Shakeup","summary":"'Breakthru Beverage Group has undergone a \"strategic review\" of the company's \"overall business,\" according to a memo sent to employees by CEO Tom Bené on Tuesday, leading to layoffs of approximately 500 people, sources confirmed to Brewbound. Employees reported layoffs in several markets on the Reddit thread r/BreakthruBev. Sources confirmed the layoffs were closer to half of the rumored 1,000 employees cut.'","requestCount":707},{"issueDateStr":"Feb 20, 2026","publicationId":3,"dataId":314247,"subtitle":"WineBusiness News","title":"New Year Brings Steady Off-Premise Sales","summary":"Dry January does not appear to have had much of an impact on off-premise spending this year","requestCount":562},{"issueDateStr":"Feb 20, 2026","publicationId":3,"dataId":314272,"subtitle":"Brooke Fanale, UC Davis","title":"UC Davis Studying Best Winery Sanitation Practices","summary":"Please take a few minutes and fill this survey if you are involved in wine production. UC Davis is studying automated cleaning systems and evaluating if they will be useful in the wine industry. This survey is to help create a techno-economic analysis (TEA) and a life cycle analysis (LCA) for cleaning in the wine industry. Data will be used academically and responses will remain anonymous.","requestCount":365},{"issueDateStr":"Feb 20, 2026","publicationId":3,"dataId":314312,"subtitle":"twitter","title":"Representative Thomas Massie (R-KY) to Introduce \"No Immunity for Glyphosate Act\"","summary":"'... to undo the recent Executive Order which promotes glyphosate (Round-Up) and insulates manufacturers from liability.'","requestCount":361},{"issueDateStr":"Feb 20, 2026","publicationId":3,"dataId":314264,"subtitle":"WineBusiness News","title":"Grapes & Bulk Wine Market Activity Rises in January","summary":"The WineBusiness Grapes & Bulk Wine Market saw increased buyer activity in January with replies to listings up 9% year-over-year despite a nearly 30% decline in posted lots. The increase was driven primarily by bulk wine, with replies up 12% versus January 2025. Shiner listings also saw increased interest, while 2026 grape listings declined. This shift toward bulk wine aligns with current market conditions where high-quality bulk wine is readily available.","requestCount":357}],"aWDay":[{"issueDateStr":"Feb 19, 2026","publicationId":3,"dataId":314206,"subtitle":"brewbound - paywall","title":"Breakthru Beverage Lays Off 500 Workers Amid Industry Shakeup","summary":"'Breakthru Beverage Group has undergone a \"strategic review\" of the company's \"overall business,\" according to a memo sent to employees by CEO Tom Bené on Tuesday, leading to layoffs of approximately 500 people, sources confirmed to Brewbound. Employees reported layoffs in several markets on the Reddit thread r/BreakthruBev. Sources confirmed the layoffs were closer to half of the rumored 1,000 employees cut.'","requestCount":2928},{"issueDateStr":"Feb 19, 2026","publicationId":3,"dataId":314213,"subtitle":"Jess Lander, SF Chronicle paywall","title":"Gallo closing the Ranch Winery, laying off workers at four other locations","summary":"Gallo is closing a Napa Valley production facility and has planned layoffs at four other California wineries and tasting rooms, resulting in the loss of 93 jobs. Gallo will permanently close the Ranch Winery and cut staff at Louis M. Martini Winery and the Orin Swift tasting room, J Vineyards and Frei Ranch, another large production facility. Layoffs will impact a variety of departments, including winemaking, hospitality and culinary.","requestCount":2855},{"issueDateStr":"Feb 20, 2026","publicationId":3,"dataId":314320,"subtitle":"NBC News","title":"Supreme Court strikes down most of Trump's tariffs in a major blow to the president","summary":"The decision does not affect all of Trump's tariffs but invalidates those implemented using an emergency law.","requestCount":2032},{"issueDateStr":"Feb 18, 2026","publicationId":3,"dataId":314151,"subtitle":"San Francisco Chronicle","title":"Chalone Vineyard Lays Off Winemaking Staff, Brand to Continue","summary":"Chalone Vineyard will no longer produce wine at its winery in Soledad (Monterey County), confirmed Nora Feeley, a spokesperson for parent company Foley Family Wines. The brand is not going anywhere, however: An offsite tasting room in Carmel-by-the-Sea will remain open, and wines from the Chalone estate vineyard will be made at other Foley facilities, which are located in Napa Valley, Sonoma County, the Central Coast and elsewhere.","requestCount":1603},{"issueDateStr":"Feb 17, 2026","publicationId":3,"dataId":314086,"subtitle":"Erica Duecy for Forbes","title":"Wine Paris 2026 Showed How The Industry Is Recalibrating","summary":"Walking the halls in Paris this week with more than 65,000 trade visitors and 6,500 exhibitors, what stood out was not anxiety, but rather adaptation. It was clear that the industry understands the scale of its structural shifts, and is actively designing around them.","requestCount":1568},{"issueDateStr":"Feb 19, 2026","publicationId":3,"dataId":314207,"subtitle":"Dave Infante","title":"Here's what Breakthru's CEO is saying about its latest layoffs","summary":"\"Shifting consumer preferences, economic pressures, and evolving marketplace dynamics are reshaping the landscape and placing sustained pressure on our business.\"","requestCount":1236}]},"aHeadings":[{"key":"aYDay","val":"Yesterday"},{"key":"aWDay","val":"Past Week"},{"key":"aMDay","val":"Past Month"}]}</script>

